WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.840 --> 00:00:07.238
Dear young people, dear believers,
today's Gospel in the first sentence

00:00:07.238 --> 00:00:14.108
tells us, Jesus truly, truly, those who
keep my words will have eternal life.

00:00:14.108 --> 00:00:21.470
If you recall when we pray the Creed,
we also profess our faith in eternal

00:00:21.470 --> 00:00:24.905
life and the resurrection of the body.

00:00:24.905 --> 00:00:31.285
However, sometimes I get the impression
that many find it hard to accept.

00:00:31.735 --> 00:00:38.564
Once, after Easter, I led a Mass just
like this one and in the sermon, I

00:00:38.564 --> 00:00:41.125
asked the people, we celebrate Easter.

00:00:41.125 --> 00:00:47.527
I asked, who among you believes that
Jesus is truly alive, that He has risen?

00:00:47.527 --> 00:00:50.088
A few people raised their hands.

00:00:50.088 --> 00:00:54.356
How many of you here tonight
believe in eternal life?

00:00:54.356 --> 00:00:55.210
First you.

00:00:59.530 --> 00:01:00.063
Great.

00:01:00.063 --> 00:01:03.264
I can change the topic then.

00:01:03.264 --> 00:01:11.268
I'm glad to see many of you believe
in eternal life, but let's see how

00:01:11.268 --> 00:01:15.003
many of you believe you'll be saved.

00:01:15.003 --> 00:01:16.070
No hands.

00:01:16.070 --> 00:01:17.137
Just kidding.

00:01:17.137 --> 00:01:20.338
Just kidding, back to the topic.

00:01:20.338 --> 00:01:24.607
So, we profess and
believe in eternal life.

00:01:24.607 --> 00:01:28.342
First of all, what should we emphasize?

00:01:28.342 --> 00:01:31.009
That we inherit eternal life.

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:38.764
Does our birth and existence in this
world have any meaning at all if

00:01:38.764 --> 00:01:41.800
we don't think about eternal life?

00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:47.872
It would perhaps be too ordinary,
too monotonous, too meaningless to be

00:01:47.872 --> 00:01:51.920
born just to die and that's the end.

00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:59.004
We are actually born to live this
life, to die, but also to pass

00:01:59.004 --> 00:02:01.534
through death into eternal life.

00:02:01.534 --> 00:02:09.125
And it is very important for us as
believers how we live our lives now.

00:02:10.405 --> 00:02:15.696
Whoever does not carry life within
themselves now will never see heaven.

00:02:15.696 --> 00:02:20.546
Many people, like the Jews in
today's Gospel, are so entrenched

00:02:20.546 --> 00:02:25.837
in earthly matters that they don't
think about eternal life at all.

00:02:25.837 --> 00:02:32.451
They neither have the time to think
about it nor do they engage with it.

00:02:32.451 --> 00:02:39.065
But you see, if we don't carry that
heaven within us now, we won't later.

00:02:40.195 --> 00:02:44.892
I always like to say that eternal
life doesn't start after you die,

00:02:44.892 --> 00:02:49.951
with God waiting up there in some
rooms to decide who goes to heaven,

00:02:49.951 --> 00:02:52.480
who to hell, and who to purgatory.

00:02:52.480 --> 00:02:54.648
Eternal life begins here on earth.

00:02:54.648 --> 00:02:58.261
That's why it's very important
for us to understand that

00:02:58.261 --> 00:03:00.429
we are not here by accident.

00:03:00.429 --> 00:03:04.765
We weren't just randomly born, living,
struggling, and praying to God to

00:03:04.765 --> 00:03:07.295
take our last breath and find rest.

00:03:08.390 --> 00:03:14.980
So, it wouldn't make sense, but if we
internalize that we were born here, we

00:03:14.980 --> 00:03:22.010
live, and for us Christians, death is not
a taboo topic, for us Christians, death is

00:03:22.010 --> 00:03:29.480
not a word we use to scare each other, yet
we increasingly live the mentality of this

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:32.556
world where we don't talk about death.

00:03:32.556 --> 00:03:38.268
When I conduct spiritual retreats,
I like to ask people, and I'll ask

00:03:38.268 --> 00:03:43.980
you here as well, how often do you
see children at funerals nowadays?

00:03:45.260 --> 00:03:47.870
Who still takes children
to funerals nowadays?

00:03:47.870 --> 00:03:51.971
Many parents will say, no, no,
no, it's not psychologically good

00:03:51.971 --> 00:03:54.209
for them, they might get scared.

00:03:54.209 --> 00:04:00.175
And then we hide it from the children,
raising the youth as if people don't die.

00:04:00.175 --> 00:04:05.768
I remember as a child, it was completely
normal that when someone in the village

00:04:05.768 --> 00:04:11.735
died, we all went to the funeral, you see
the coffin, you see the deceased person.

00:04:12.095 --> 00:04:16.860
And now, now when I'm at
funerals, you rarely see children.

00:04:16.860 --> 00:04:20.326
Because we hide from
children that people die.

00:04:20.326 --> 00:04:25.092
And then we wonder where our
fear of death comes from?

00:04:25.092 --> 00:04:30.291
We present this world as if
there is no death, no illness.

00:04:30.291 --> 00:04:37.224
Yet Jesus himself came to die, to open
heaven for us and give us eternal life.

00:04:37.224 --> 00:04:41.990
Even Jesus died and was in
the grave for three days.

00:04:42.969 --> 00:04:47.272
And sometimes we want to hide all of that.

00:04:47.272 --> 00:04:52.053
It's very important how we
live in the present moment.

00:04:52.053 --> 00:04:55.400
How we perceive death and our transition.

00:04:55.400 --> 00:05:01.615
Because the way we live our life,
that's how our death will be.

00:05:01.615 --> 00:05:06.874
Some people die in fear of death,
while others die peacefully.

00:05:06.874 --> 00:05:10.699
Those who die peacefully,
calmly, serenely, they already

00:05:10.699 --> 00:05:13.090
had a relationship with God.

00:05:13.090 --> 00:05:15.354
They lived this moment wisely.

00:05:15.354 --> 00:05:22.150
And now I come to what I want
to say: How to earn that heaven?

00:05:22.150 --> 00:05:24.868
How to earn that eternal life?

00:05:24.868 --> 00:05:28.039
And that communion with Jesus in heaven.

00:05:28.039 --> 00:05:34.381
Well, the servant of God, I believe
many of you have read his works,

00:05:34.381 --> 00:05:39.817
Fulton Sheen, gives us excellent
advice on how to get to heaven.

00:05:39.817 --> 00:05:47.065
And he says this: if you want to get
to heaven, then take someone with you.

00:05:47.865 --> 00:05:52.886
If you want to get to heaven,
then take someone with you.

00:05:52.886 --> 00:05:54.979
And what does that mean?

00:05:54.979 --> 00:06:00.419
In the Holy Scripture, it says, you
will recognize them by their fruits.

00:06:00.419 --> 00:06:04.185
Our desire should be
to love what God loves.

00:06:04.185 --> 00:06:06.278
And what does God love?

00:06:06.278 --> 00:06:09.626
God loves for every person to be saved.

00:06:09.626 --> 00:06:16.740
And that's why it's our duty, and that's
why this servant of God says, if you want

00:06:16.740 --> 00:06:19.670
to earn heaven, take someone with you.

00:06:19.670 --> 00:06:25.394
On the other hand, we should care
and feel for people who are unaware

00:06:25.394 --> 00:06:30.710
of the moment they are living in,
that minutes are passing by and

00:06:30.710 --> 00:06:33.981
every day we are closer to the grave.

00:06:33.981 --> 00:06:39.296
We shouldn't be afraid of time passing,
of aging, or of death approaching.

00:06:39.296 --> 00:06:44.612
But we should be afraid if we
don't help others reach heaven, if

00:06:44.612 --> 00:06:49.110
we don't guide others to eternal
life because we remain silent.

00:06:51.435 --> 00:06:56.410
Isn't it funny that today many
families spend more time and care

00:06:56.410 --> 00:07:01.799
arranging a restaurant for the wake
than they do for the spiritual state

00:07:01.799 --> 00:07:07.189
of the deceased, how they will die
spiritually, in what condition they die.

00:07:07.189 --> 00:07:12.579
We are more preoccupied with organizing
the funeral, even though we know we

00:07:12.579 --> 00:07:16.310
have a person in the house who is dying.

00:07:16.310 --> 00:07:19.627
Who hasn't received confession,
hasn't received Jesus, hasn't

00:07:19.627 --> 00:07:22.115
received the anointing of the sick.

00:07:22.115 --> 00:07:25.392
And what do you say to us then?

00:07:25.392 --> 00:07:29.488
We didn't call you so the
person wouldn't get scared.

00:07:29.488 --> 00:07:33.994
As if we priests bring
death, and even if we did.

00:07:33.994 --> 00:07:38.500
How can you be afraid of
the Anointing of the Sick?

00:07:38.500 --> 00:07:45.464
What kind of excuses are these and what
kind of love is that for a dying person?

00:07:45.464 --> 00:07:49.970
Where is this sentence from Fulton
Sheen, "lead someone to heaven"?

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:54.886
If we let our sick die without
the sacrament, equipped, and then

00:07:54.886 --> 00:07:59.801
swear by love and organize wakes
and pay for the best catering,

00:07:59.801 --> 00:08:01.850
that won't help the deceased.

00:08:03.190 --> 00:08:07.133
Tell me, who benefits from
love that comes too late?

00:08:07.133 --> 00:08:10.287
Love that comes too late helps no one.

00:08:10.287 --> 00:08:14.230
When I die, and everything
that is done afterward, that's

00:08:14.230 --> 00:08:16.202
love that comes too late.

00:08:16.202 --> 00:08:22.117
So if we have love for our loved
ones, if we want to send someone

00:08:22.117 --> 00:08:26.848
to heaven, then we should show
them love while they are alive.

00:08:26.848 --> 00:08:28.426
Gradually prepare the person.

00:08:28.426 --> 00:08:31.974
We should start by frequently
thinking about death ourselves.

00:08:31.974 --> 00:08:38.222
Because one saint beautifully said that
a Christian is not true if they don't at

00:08:38.222 --> 00:08:41.554
least once remember that they have to die.

00:08:41.554 --> 00:08:41.971
Why?

00:08:41.971 --> 00:08:47.802
If you think about death, you prepare
yourself and then you are not afraid.

00:08:47.802 --> 00:08:54.467
If you neglect this topic, if you hide
it from children, if you hide it from

00:08:54.467 --> 00:09:00.715
the sick, of course, it becomes a shock,
because no one here will live forever.

00:09:01.375 --> 00:09:07.663
And what is common to all of us,
both the poor and the rich, the

00:09:07.663 --> 00:09:10.179
famous and the unknown, is death.

00:09:10.179 --> 00:09:13.533
But do you know what sets us apart?

00:09:13.533 --> 00:09:19.403
What sets us apart is that we will
all die, but faith distinguishes us.

00:09:19.403 --> 00:09:24.434
Some will die, but some will have
faith and will be resurrected.

00:09:24.434 --> 00:09:28.207
That is the difference among
all people, regardless of

00:09:28.207 --> 00:09:29.885
nationality, race, or status.

00:09:29.885 --> 00:09:34.019
We all die, my dear, but not
everyone will be resurrected.

00:09:34.019 --> 00:09:38.154
Those who have prepared themselves
will be resurrected, those who have

00:09:38.154 --> 00:09:40.785
made ready, and not avoided this topic.

00:09:40.785 --> 00:09:43.040
That's why I brought it up.

00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:47.927
That's why Jesus says tonight, truly,
truly I say to you, whoever keeps

00:09:47.927 --> 00:09:50.182
my word will have eternal life.

00:09:50.182 --> 00:09:55.445
Even the Jews can't believe what He
is talking about, that He knows God.

00:09:57.065 --> 00:10:04.421
If we haven't met God the Father here
on earth, we won't meet Him when we die.

00:10:04.421 --> 00:10:11.345
So, the problem isn't with our enemies;
the problem is if we are our own enemies.

00:10:11.345 --> 00:10:16.538
If I'm not honest with myself
and my time is passing, can

00:10:16.538 --> 00:10:19.134
any of us bring back yesterday?

00:10:19.134 --> 00:10:25.193
We can't, but it will await you
when you stand before God and how

00:10:25.193 --> 00:10:28.655
you lived that day, each one of us.

00:10:29.990 --> 00:10:34.824
Saint Paul says, "My desire is
to depart and be with Christ."

00:10:34.824 --> 00:10:36.839
See how the saints think.

00:10:36.839 --> 00:10:43.285
"My desire is to depart and be with
Christ." Do we have the desire to die?

00:10:43.285 --> 00:10:49.732
Because do we understand that our dying
is a passage to eternal life, not the end?

00:10:49.732 --> 00:10:54.970
The one who believes that when they
exhale their last breath and die,

00:10:54.970 --> 00:10:59.805
that it is the end of everything,
is obviously not a Christian.

00:11:00.665 --> 00:11:02.149
A Christian has hope.

00:11:02.149 --> 00:11:07.718
And that is what Jesus said, I am
going to prepare a place for you.

00:11:07.718 --> 00:11:09.945
So we deserve heaven through Jesus.

00:11:09.945 --> 00:11:13.286
I am going to prepare a place for you.

00:11:13.286 --> 00:11:16.256
In my Father's house,
there are many rooms.

00:11:16.256 --> 00:11:18.112
See how wonderful that is.

00:11:18.112 --> 00:11:23.310
And then when you see all the
saints, like Saint Paul, who said, I

00:11:23.310 --> 00:11:25.908
desire to depart and be with Christ.

00:11:25.908 --> 00:11:29.621
We humans live here to
die, to be with Christ.

00:11:29.621 --> 00:11:30.734
Do you understand?

00:11:30.734 --> 00:11:35.189
We live here, we struggle so
that we can die, to ultimately

00:11:35.189 --> 00:11:36.674
be eternally with Christ.

00:11:36.674 --> 00:11:38.902
So why the fear around death?

00:11:38.902 --> 00:11:44.841
How much do we fear this topic, how
much do we fear this experience, and we

00:11:44.841 --> 00:11:48.182
don't want to open up or talk about it?

00:11:48.182 --> 00:11:50.781
And then we always have our excuses.

00:11:50.781 --> 00:11:56.350
We are young, it's not the time to
talk about it, I'll do it later.

00:11:56.610 --> 00:11:59.502
The sun, when it prepares for death?

00:11:59.502 --> 00:12:06.938
It seems to me that in Croatia, it's most
often when you end up on machines and when

00:12:06.938 --> 00:12:10.243
you can't speak, bound by all the tubes.

00:12:10.243 --> 00:12:11.896
Then it's too late.

00:12:11.896 --> 00:12:16.440
Even if you're young, because every
minute echoes later in heaven.

00:12:16.440 --> 00:12:18.506
How do you live them?

00:12:18.506 --> 00:12:20.985
So now, every day is constant.

00:12:20.985 --> 00:12:27.182
Let's not leave it until we grow
old, until we get sick, and here, I

00:12:27.182 --> 00:12:32.553
say, most often we start preparing
to meet God and transition, that is,

00:12:32.553 --> 00:12:37.924
to pass into eternity, when we are
completely sick and can't do anything

00:12:37.924 --> 00:12:39.990
anymore, and then we remember.

00:12:39.990 --> 00:12:45.702
Saint Ignatius of Antioch writes to
the Christian community and says, "How

00:12:45.702 --> 00:12:54.270
beautiful it is to set like the sun in
this world, so that we may rise in the

00:12:54.270 --> 00:13:01.887
heavenly dawn with God. How beautiful
it is to set in this world to awaken in

00:13:01.887 --> 00:13:05.695
the presence of God." And what is that?

00:13:05.695 --> 00:13:07.123
Dying to oneself.

00:13:07.123 --> 00:13:12.359
Every day when you take care,
prepare, and as I mentioned

00:13:12.359 --> 00:13:14.740
earlier, that is our setting.

00:13:14.740 --> 00:13:19.253
But you will dawn in the presence of God.

00:13:19.253 --> 00:13:23.265
And see how beautifully the saints put it.

00:13:23.265 --> 00:13:30.285
There was a professor at the university
who wrote a farewell letter to her

00:13:30.285 --> 00:13:37.306
colleagues, and it goes like this: I
will cherish the moment when you read

00:13:37.306 --> 00:13:43.825
this letter of mine in church, because
before you go on summer vacation,

00:13:43.825 --> 00:13:50.846
I want you to know the truth about
me, which I learned last Friday.

00:13:50.846 --> 00:13:55.861
The doctor finally told me my
true diagnosis, cancer that

00:13:55.861 --> 00:13:58.870
can no longer be operated on.

00:13:59.459 --> 00:14:05.234
If he had been a Christian, he surely
wouldn't have been so shaken, nor would

00:14:05.234 --> 00:14:11.008
he have delayed so much in telling me
the truth, because he would know, as

00:14:11.008 --> 00:14:17.552
you and I know, that we face both death
and life equally if we live in God's

00:14:17.552 --> 00:14:19.861
presence and according to His will.

00:14:19.861 --> 00:14:26.405
If God has decided that I will soon be
with Him, I am joyful because of it.

00:14:26.405 --> 00:14:30.255
Please, do not grieve
for me for even a moment.

00:14:30.655 --> 00:14:37.373
I do not bid you a cold farewell with
this goodbye, but rather send you a

00:14:37.373 --> 00:14:44.092
warm greeting until we meet again in the
blessed land where I may be allowed to

00:14:44.092 --> 00:14:47.031
lift the veil when you are departing.

00:14:47.031 --> 00:14:51.650
With a heart full of
greetings for each one of you.

00:14:51.650 --> 00:14:55.010
I bid you farewell, your
friend and colleague.

00:14:55.290 --> 00:14:59.103
Two weeks after that
letter, she passed away.

00:14:59.103 --> 00:15:05.300
So, this is an example of a
person who lives their faith, who

00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:11.021
is not afraid of death because
they know where they are going.

00:15:11.021 --> 00:15:13.881
They are transitioning to eternal life.

00:15:13.881 --> 00:15:18.171
You also have the experience
of Pope John XXIII.

00:15:18.171 --> 00:15:21.985
He viewed the transition
of death so optimistically.

00:15:21.985 --> 00:15:28.658
And when he fell ill, the doctors
didn't want to tell him the full

00:15:28.658 --> 00:15:34.856
diagnosis to encourage him, but when
they told him a milder version of

00:15:34.856 --> 00:15:41.529
his illness, not the truth, he told
them they didn't need to hide it,

00:15:41.529 --> 00:15:44.390
saying, "My affairs are in order."

00:15:44.390 --> 00:15:50.293
And then his secretary came to him
again, and he said, I am completely

00:15:50.293 --> 00:15:55.354
at peace, should I be afraid
to hear the Lord's words, today

00:15:55.354 --> 00:15:58.305
you will be with me in paradise.

00:15:58.305 --> 00:16:04.209
And how many such people do we know, our
grandmothers, relatives, who had faith

00:16:04.209 --> 00:16:07.583
and who died and who wanted to die.

00:16:07.583 --> 00:16:10.535
Today, we do everything to avoid dying.

00:16:11.995 --> 00:16:17.562
I have often said in my sermons
when I go to bless houses,

00:16:17.562 --> 00:16:19.275
that is everyone's intention.

00:16:19.275 --> 00:16:21.417
Child, pray for my health.

00:16:21.417 --> 00:16:23.987
Just so I can live longer.

00:16:23.987 --> 00:16:31.268
That is nice and necessary, but I say
that God is still waiting for us up there.

00:16:31.268 --> 00:16:37.692
And that we need to have faith no
matter how and how long we live.

00:16:37.692 --> 00:16:44.116
If you listened to this letter, I really
like that it highlighted and said, I

00:16:44.116 --> 00:16:47.115
greet you with goodbye, not with God.

00:16:47.475 --> 00:16:49.870
Goodbye, until the next meeting.

00:16:49.870 --> 00:16:54.661
We bid farewell to our deceased
until the next meeting.

00:16:54.661 --> 00:17:01.847
Now I ask you, we profess, as I mentioned
earlier, in the belief of eternal

00:17:01.847 --> 00:17:05.201
life and the resurrection of the body.

00:17:05.201 --> 00:17:10.950
How wonderful it would be if we
Christians, who believe in eternal

00:17:10.950 --> 00:17:16.699
life after death and the resurrection,
and in eternal life, bear witness,

00:17:16.699 --> 00:17:19.095
bear witness wherever we are.

00:17:21.984 --> 00:17:30.434
How nice it would be if on our tombstones,
when we erect monuments for our deceased,

00:17:30.434 --> 00:17:37.299
it said "here awaits the resurrection"
instead of "forever with God." We cannot

00:17:37.299 --> 00:17:40.468
write "forever with God" on tombstones.

00:17:40.468 --> 00:17:46.805
It should only say "this one
awaits" or "this one awaits the

00:17:46.805 --> 00:17:49.446
resurrection." That is a testimony.

00:17:49.446 --> 00:17:57.367
When we buried our deceased and loved
ones, we believe in "until we meet again"

00:17:57.367 --> 00:18:03.705
and not "forever with God" and those
dramatic phrases we sometimes write.

00:18:04.605 --> 00:18:09.611
That is why it is important,
when you listen to the Mass, we

00:18:09.611 --> 00:18:13.076
have these Eucharistic prayers,
the first, second, and third.

00:18:13.076 --> 00:18:18.082
In the third Eucharistic prayer, it says,
"And our deceased brothers and sisters,

00:18:18.082 --> 00:18:23.088
all who have passed from this world
in your love, graciously receive them

00:18:23.088 --> 00:18:28.480
into your kingdom, where we also hope
to enjoy your glory with them forever."

00:18:29.440 --> 00:18:34.616
Where we also hope to enjoy
eternal glory together with them.

00:18:34.616 --> 00:18:37.910
And what is important, dear young people?

00:18:37.910 --> 00:18:43.557
Maybe some of you study philosophy
and know philosophy and such things

00:18:43.557 --> 00:18:50.145
better than I do, but surely you
have all heard the story about the

00:18:50.145 --> 00:18:54.851
philosopher Diogenes, the Greek
philosopher who decided to sell wisdom.

00:18:54.851 --> 00:19:01.440
And of course, he set up a stand
where he sold wisdom, and everyone...

00:19:01.620 --> 00:19:07.079
They laughed and mocked him, but
eventually, a man with his servants

00:19:07.079 --> 00:19:13.447
came by and was curious about what
this wisdom he was selling looked like.

00:19:13.447 --> 00:19:19.816
So, he gave his servant three coins
to go and buy wisdom from him.

00:19:19.816 --> 00:19:26.640
The servant went, and the philosopher told
him to repeat three times to his master:

00:19:26.640 --> 00:19:30.280
in everything you do, think of your end.

00:19:30.630 --> 00:19:34.545
In everything you do,
think about your end.

00:19:34.545 --> 00:19:38.460
In everything you think,
think about your end.

00:19:38.460 --> 00:19:38.950
Amen.

